{
  "hooks": {
    "SessionStart": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "$HOME/.keel/hooks/session-start.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PreToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Write|Edit",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "$HOME/.keel/hooks/pre-tool-use.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Write|Edit",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "$HOME/.keel/hooks/post-tool-use.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "Stop": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "prompt",
            "prompt": "This is a hook evaluation — not a user message. Scan the preceding assistant response for signals and reply with valid JSON only — no plain text, no explanation, no markdown.\n\nSignals to detect (be conservative — only flag clear, unambiguous cases):\n(1) ARCHITECTURE — a significant, non-reversible technical choice with explicit trade-offs was made (e.g. chose Redis over Memcached, adopted hexagonal arch, set a hard constraint). Do NOT flag routine implementation, bug fixes, refactors, or adding a function.\n(2) DOC GAP — a net-new HTTP route, CLI flag, env var, or infra component was added. Do NOT flag edits to existing routes, refactors, or internal function changes.\n(3) SECURITY — auth, authorization, payments, PII handling, crypto, or secrets management was the central focus of the change.\n\nReply format — output ONLY one of these, nothing else:\n• No signals detected: {\"ok\": true}\n• One or more signals: {\"ok\": false, \"reason\": \"<signals joined by \\\\n>\"}\n\nSignal strings to use:\n• Architecture (decision with trade-offs): 💡 ADR candidate — run /keel:adr to capture this decision.\n• Architecture (hard constraint / new feature scope): 💡 PRD candidate — run /keel:prd to capture it. or 💡 Invariant candidate — run /keel:invariant to capture this constraint.\n• Doc gap: 📄 Doc gap: <specific thing added> — run /keel:docs to review.\n• Security: 🔒 Security-sensitive change — run /keel:audit before shipping.\n\nIMPORTANT: Your entire response must be a single line of valid JSON. No text before or after the JSON."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PreCompact": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "$HOME/.keel/hooks/pre-compact.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
